{
  "_comment": [
    "Forker template. Copy to registries.auto.tfvars.json at the repo root",
    "(the real file is gitignored by the *.tfvars.json rule — ECR account IDs",
    "are sensitive and stay out of git). The Makefile / CI passes it to the",
    "regional env via -var-file.",
    "",
    "This is NOT the workload catalog — ArgoCD discovers workloads by the",
    "`aegis-workload` GitHub topic (ADR-07). This map holds only what discovery",
    "cannot supply: the ECR registry to inject (account-ID hide) and opt-in",
    "engine IRSA params. Onboarding a workload using private ECR = tag the repo",
    "+ add one entry here, keyed by deploy-repo name.",
    "",
    "engine_irsa is OPTIONAL — declare it only for a workload whose engine",
    "ServiceAccount needs an ACK-provisioned IAM role. The ApplicationSet",
    "injects the role-arn annotation, building the ARN from the cluster account",
    "(so no account ID is hardcoded in the public deploy repo). role_name must",
    "match the path+name in the deploy repo's ACK Role CRD.",
    "",
    "ingress_cert is OPTIONAL — declare ingress_name for a workload with a TLS",
    "ALB gateway. WS3-R: the platform provisions a PER-REGION cert (regional",
    "acm.tf) and the ApplicationSet injects that region's ARN automatically, so",
    "cert_arn should be OMITTED. Set cert_arn only to override with your own cert",
    "(it then must be a region-correct, cluster-account ACM ARN).",
    "",
    "ADR-10 — ONE shared registry for ALL clusters. ecr_account_id now points",
    "at the dedicated aegis-deployment account (Deployments OU), NOT a per-",
    "environment workload account. Staging + prod, every region, inject the SAME",
    "registry here and pull the same immutable digest the build pushed once. The",
    "old per-account model (ecr_account_id = each env's own account) is replaced;",
    "the build-once/promote-by-digest invariant means every cluster resolves the",
    "same <deployment-account-id>.dkr.ecr.<region>.amazonaws.com/<repo>.",
    "",
    "WS3-R — aegis-core wiring (mostly automatic now):",
    "  engine_irsa.policy_arns = [<model_read_policy_arn>]  (engine reads the S3",
    "    model bucket; the ApplicationSet injects it onto the WorkloadIdentity",
    "    Claim's policyArns, so the account-bound ARN stays out of the public repo).",
    "  ingress_cert.cert_arn — OMIT: the per-region module cert (regional acm.tf)",
    "    is injected automatically; pin only to override with your own cert.",
    "  ecr_region — value here is just a default; envs/regional overrides it to",
    "    the per-apply region so each cluster pulls from its in-region replica.",
    "  ConfigMaps are filled automatically by the ApplicationSet from the platform",
    "    outputs (model_bucket_name, Cognito issuer/audience/jwks) — no hand-patch."
  ],
  "workload_registries": {
    "aegis-greeter-deploy": {
      "ecr_account_id": "<deployment-account-id>",
      "ecr_region": "eu-central-1"
    },
    "aegis-core-deploy": {
      "ecr_account_id": "<deployment-account-id>",
      "ecr_region": "eu-central-1",
      "engine_irsa": {
        "service_account": "aegis-core-engine",
        "role_name": "aegis-workload/aegis-core-engine",
        "policy_arns": ["arn:aws:iam::<cluster-account-id>:policy/aegis-core-model-read"]
      },
      "ingress_cert": {
        "ingress_name": "aegis-core-gateway"
      }
    }
  }
}
